# blocked-paths — file paths the pre-commit hook will block from being committed.
# One POSIX extended regex per line, matched against staged file paths
# (the output of `git diff --cached --name-only --diff-filter=AM`).
# Lines starting with # are comments. Blank lines ignored.
#
# When a staged path matches any pattern, the commit is blocked with a dialog
# (macOS) and terminal output, giving you three choices: keep blocked, unstage,
# or commit anyway.
#
# Belt-and-suspenders companion to ~/.gitignore_global: the global gitignore
# silently refuses to stage; this hook also catches files that were force-added
# or were already tracked.
#
# Nothing is blocked by default. Uncomment lines that apply to you and add your
# own. A few neutral examples to start from:

#   (^|/)\.claude(/|$)
#   (^|/)private(/|$)
#   (^|/)NOTES\.md$
